2a:["$","p","35",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Once you've played a set of 7-inch singles, building the tracklist is the next challenge. Many classic funk and soul 7-inches have worn or illegible labels. <strong class=\"text-white\">45 Mix Trackr</strong> can fingerprint your recorded set and identify the tracks automatically — even from vinyl recordings with surface noise."}}]
2b:["$","hr","36",{"className":"border-[#282828] my-8"}]
2c:["$","h2","37",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"Conclusion"}]
2d:["$","p","38",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"A 45 RPM adapter is one of the smallest but most important pieces of gear in a vinyl DJ's arsenal. For durability and stability, the Nagaoka Spider or a metal screw-in adapter are the top picks. For budget-conscious DJs spinning occasionally, the classic red plastic inserts get the job done perfectly."}}]
2e:["$","p","39",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Don't let a $2 accessory ruin a set — always pack extras."}}]
